    <h2><strong>What is functional fragrance?</strong> </h2>
    <p>In daily life, our sense of smell plays a vital role in determining our sense of well being. How we feel and how we remember is often linked to a certain scent. For example, a hint of blooming jasmine from a nearby garden floats by and suddenly it’s spring, you’re 15, about to have your first kiss. You notice that the scent and its memory makes you feel happy and alive. </p>
    <p>When your olfactory system is used (aka your sense of scent), certain smells can cue, evoke, and alleviate certain moods and emotions. Shown in countless studies, essential oils such as lavender, jasmine, and patchouli have been proven to help with depression, anxiety, and insomnia. Central to many cultures for thousands of years, aromatic oils such as sandalwood, amber, and bergamot have been used for a variety of therapeutic, ceremonial, and cosmetic intentions. Continuing in this ancient tradition is functional fragrance, which brings aroma, ritual, and remedy together into one space. </p>
</div>

