    <h2><strong>Why knowing your skin type matters</strong></h2>
    <p>It's not about vanity; it's about finding effective skincare products and putting your money where it matters. Understanding whether you have oily, normal, dry, combination, or sensitive skin will help you nail down your skincare routine to address its specific needs and concerns. By choosing the right, skintentional products and treatments, you can achieve optimal results and get that healthy, youthful complexion you desire.</p>

    <h2><strong>The 5 main skin types:</strong></h2>
    <p>It’s important to remember that, while there are 5 skin categories, not everyone fits neatly into one. However, identifying the category closest to your skin type empowers you to make informed decisions based on general guidelines.</p>

    <h3 style="padding-top:20px;"><strong>Oily Skin Type:</strong></h3>
    <p>If your skin tends to shine brighter than a diamond, you may have oily skin. Oily skin is characterized by excess oil or sebum production, leading to a shiny complexion, enlarged pores, and a propensity for blackheads. Combat oiliness with effective cleansers, non-comedogenic moisturizers, and mattifying sunscreens. Read our recommended oily skincare routine <a href="https://www.pacificabeauty.com/blogs/the-compassionista/skincare-routine-for-oily-and-acne-prone-skin">here.</a></p>
    <p><strong>Recommended products:</strong> Pacifica Beauty’s <a href="https://www.pacificabeauty.com/collections/kale-skincare">Kale</a> and <a href="https://www.pacificabeauty.com/collections/acne">Acne Warrior</a> products are ideal for oily and acne-prone skin to deeply decongest and target acne breakouts. Our vitamin C powered <a href="https://www.pacificabeauty.com/collections/glow-baby">Glow Baby collection</a> helps address hyperpigmentation, soothe post-inflammation, and slough off dead skin with exfoliating AHAs.</p>
</div>

