<div class="article__section-container">
    <h2><strong>How to determine your skin type</strong></h2>
    <p>Not sure what your skin type is? Decoding your skin type is actually easier than you think! Follow these simple steps to determine which category your skin falls into:</p>
    <ol class="list-no-style list-indent">
        <li><h3 style="padding-top:20px;"><strong>Cleanse your face thoroughly with a mild cleanser to remove impurities.</strong></h3></li>
        <li><h3 style="padding-top:20px;"><strong>Pat your skin dry with a clean towel and wait 30 minutes to an hour.</strong></h3></li>
        <li><h3 style="padding-top:20px;"><strong>Observe how your skin feels and looks:</strong></h3></li>
    </ol>
    <ul class="list-show-bullet">
        <li>Normal skin feels balanced, neither too oily nor too dry.</li>
        <li>Oily skin appears shiny and may have visible pores.</li>
        <li>Dry skin feels tight, looks dull, and may have flaky patches.</li>
        <li>Combination skin is shiny in certain areas, yet dry in others.</li>
        <li>Sensitive skin is reactive, exhibiting signs of irritation like redness, itching, or stinging.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2><strong>Common skincare mistakes to avoid for each skin type</strong></h2>
    <h3 style="padding-top:20px;"><strong>Over-cleansing:</strong></h3>
    <p>Over-drying is overrated! Stripping the skin of its natural oils can exacerbate dryness and disrupt the skin’s natural barrier, which can lead to increased oil production and breakouts. There’s even research that points to increased chances of premature aging from the wear and tear of over-cleansed skin!</p>
    
    <h3 style="padding-top:20px;"><strong>Skipping sunscreen:</strong></h3>
    <p>What do these routines each have in common? SPF! Regardless of your skin type, sunscreen is non-negotiable for protecting against UV damage and premature aging. Read about the importance of sun protection <a href="https://www.pacificabeauty.com/blogs/the-compassionista/vitamin-c-and-sunscreen-can-you-mix-these-two-ingredients">here</a>.</p>
    
    <h3 style="padding-top:20px;"><strong>Using harsh ingredients:</strong></h3>
    <p>No matter your skin’s sensitivity, we believe that what we put onto our skin is as important as what we put in our bodies and into the environment. Avoid skincare products with harsh toxins such as parabens, phthalates, sulfates, silicones, or talc, all ingredients Pacifica Beauty bans, which can irritate skin, disrupt the natural skin barrier, and are toxic to the environment.</p>
</div>

