    <p>Sensitive skin is like the diva of the skincare world, with its own set of demands and triggers. But fear not, with the right care and attention, you can keep your sensitive skin calm, cool, and collected. We've got the inside scoop on how to pamper and nurture your delicate dermis.</p>

    <h2><strong>Understanding Sensitive Skin</strong></h2>
    <p>So, what exactly is sensitive skin? A sensitive skin type is like the canary in the coal mine, outwardly alerting you via reactive signs when it’s unhappy. Common triggers include everything from weather conditions to harsh ingredients, fragrances, and even stress. Signs and symptoms may include redness, itching, burning, inflammation, and dryness, but everyone's skin reacts differently, so it's essential to pay attention to what yours is telling you.</p>
    <p>Sensitive skin symptoms can also be a result of a damaged skin barrier, the outermost epidermal layer that works by retaining hydration and protecting the skin against potential hazards. Damage to your natural skin barrier can occur from a variety of factors such as harsh products, environmental stress, moisture loss, UV radiation, chemical irritants, and over-exfoliation. If you think you have barrier damage, don’t fret! With proper tender loving care, the skin barrier can be repaired and its function restored to its healthy, supply self. <br><br>To determine your skin type, <a href="https://www.pacificabeauty.com/blogs/the-compassionista/what-is-my-skin-type-an-expert-guide">read this article.</a></p>
