    <h2><strong>Choosing the Right Vitamin C and Sunscreen <br class="hidden-phone">Products for Your Skin Type</strong></h2>
    <h3 style="padding-top:10px;"><strong>The 3 main factors to consider when choosing vitamin C:</strong></h3>
    <ul class="list-no-style">
        <li><strong>Formula:</strong> Vitamin C comes in various forms, and each formula will offer its own unique benefits. To choose one that suits your individual skin needs and preferences, seek out products enriched with complementary ingredients like kakadu plum, apple cell extract, glycolic acid, hyaluronic acid, and vitamin E, all which enhance the antioxidant properties of vitamin C and boost hydration.</li>
        <li><strong>Stability:</strong> Look for stabilized vitamin C product formulations that are less prone to oxidation and degradation, such as ascorbic acid, magnesium ascorbyl phosphate, or sodium ascorbyl phosphate, to ensure potency and longevity over time.</li>
        <li><strong>Skin Sensitivity:</strong> Our products are formulated to be safe and effective for all skin types, but everyone’s skin is unique. If you have sensitive skin, opt for a patch test before incorporating your new vitamin C into your routine.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2><strong>Selecting the Best Sunscreen:</strong></h2>
    <p>In finding the perfect sunscreen products for you, it’s important to look for formulas that best suit you, work in your routine, and that deliver the benefits you desire.</p>
    <ul class="list-no-style">
        <li><strong>SPF Ratings:</strong> Opt for a broad-spectrum sunscreen with an SPF (Sun Protection Factor) of at least 30 to shield your skin from both UVA and UVB rays effectively. Higher SPF ratings provide greater protection, but SPF 30 is considered the minimum recommendation by dermatologists.</li>
        <li><strong>Mineral vs. Chemical Sunscreens:</strong> Mineral sunscreens contain active ingredients like zinc oxide, which create a physical skin barrier to deflect UV rays. The other option is chemical sunscreens, which absorb UV radiation. We offer both mineral and chemical sunscreens at Pacifica.</li>
        <li><strong>Skin Type Compatibility:</strong> Consider your skin type and specific skin concern when selecting a sunscreen. For oily or acne-prone skin, opt for lightweight, non-comedogenic formulas. Dry or sensitive skin may benefit from sunscreens enriched with hydrating ingredients such as hyaluronic acid and aloe vera. Pacifica makes this choice easier for you by formulating sunscreens that are safe and effective for all skin types. Trying to determine what your skin type is? Read our comprehensive guide to figuring out your skin type to find the ideal products for you.</li>
